{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place 450 g of the water into mixing bowl and heat <b>9 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add dashi powder and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b> or until dissolved. Transfer into a jug and set aside to cool completely (approx. 1 hour ).","Place eggs into mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 2<b>.","Add cooled dashi stock, soy sauce, rice wine and salt and mix <strong>10 sec\/speed 2<\/strong>, or until combined. Strain custard mixture through a fine mesh sieve into a jug and set aside. Rinse mixing bowl.","Divide mushrooms and prawns equally between 4 ramekins (6-8 cm, ensuring ramekins fit comfortably in Varoma dish). Gently pour custard mixture into ramekins and cover each ramekin with aluminium foil.","Place remaining 600 g water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma dish into position and place ramekins into Varoma dish. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>12 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove Varoma lid and carefully rotate custards to ensure even cooking. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>6 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>, or until custards are set and a toothpick inserted into the centre comes out clean. Carefully remove from Varoma and garnish with spring onions\/shallots and serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1050 g water","1 tsp dashi powder (see Tips)","4 eggs","2 tsp soy sauce","1 tbsp rice wine","¼ tsp salt","3 fresh shiitake mushrooms, stems removed and cups cut into slices (approx. 5 mm)","8 peeled raw prawns (approx. 100 g)","2 spring onions\/shallots, cut into thin slices"]}],"id":"r129211","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-0qvWXpszeJk\/XZMuAjm-XNI\/AAAAAAAAaAI\/3J6mg1JGl1c27JHEdj19xLNUPJ6dt3K1QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_6yjEUCasaRpmCPnS.png","title":"Chawanmushi (Japanese savoury custard)","publishedAt":"2017-12-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"12.8 g","fat":"5.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"0.8 g","calories":"427.9 kJ \/ 101.9 kcal"},"usefulItems":"jug, fine mesh sieve, aluminium foil, toothpick, ramekins (6 cm)","hintsAndTricks":["Chawanmushi meaning \"tea cup\" or \"steamed in a bowl\", is an egg custard dish popular in Japan. It is usually eaten as a starter or part of a larger meal. And it is one of the few traditional Japanese dishes eaten with a spoon!","Dashi is a Japanese stock or broth made from kombu (dried kelp), Bonito flakes (dried and smoked skipjack tuna shaved into thin flakes), anchovies, sardines or a combination of all of the above. Dashi is a fundamental ingredient in many Japanese dishes and can be found at Asian grocers and some major supermarkets."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 45m","4 portions"]}